 Bank, where, for the first time in his life, he was treated as a great man of letters. Here, too, are all the circumstances surrounding Wright's mysterious death, which many close to him regarded as suspicious.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican American authorsvBiography. 0aAmericanszFrancezParisxHistoryy20th century. 0aAuthors, Americany20th centuryvBiography. 0aAuthors, Irishy20th centuryvBiography. 0aIrishzFrancezParisxHistoryy20th century. 0aLiterature publishingzFrancezParisxHistoryy20th century. 4aAmerican. 4aGeneral. 4aLiterary Criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh1 aCampbell, James, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052023441340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052035273540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520352735423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520352735/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles